        {
          "kind": "about-group",
          "title": "About the Course",
          "entries": [
            {
              "title": "About the Course",
              "content": "Students study a life by Plutarch for two terms and spend the other term exploring the history and structure of Canada's constitutional monarchy.\n\nThis topic is included in the following course(s): Citizenship: Grade 9 (Canada)"
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "kind": "tips-group",
          "title": "Placement & Combining Tips",
          "entries": [
            {
              "title": "Placement & Combining Tips",
              "content": "The book Canada's Constitutional Monarchy is intended to be read over two years (Grades 8 and 9). However, since this is the first year this book will be used in the curriculum, Grades 8 and 9 will have the same readings in 2026-2027.\nIf a student hasn't studied Canada's government yet, consider having them take the Grade 7 government course first."
            }
          ]
        },
